- The integer array parameter `arr` must not be null.
- The integer parameter `k` is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to the length of the integer array `arr`.
- The integer array result is of length `k`.
- All values in the integer array result are unique.
- The values in the integer array result are the `k` strongest values in the array `arr` based on the given criteria.
- The median `m` of the array `arr` is calculated as the element at position `((n - 1) / 2)` in the sorted list, where `n` is the length of the array `arr`.
- For each pair of values `arr[i]` and `arr[j]`, if `|arr[i] - m| > |arr[j] - m|`, then `arr[i]` is considered stronger than `arr[j]`.
- If `|arr[i] - m| == |arr[j] - m|`, then `arr[i]` is considered stronger than `arr[j]` if `arr[i] > arr[j]`.
- The order of the elements in the result array is arbitrary.